Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into small 1cm
chunks.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and pepper chunks. Fry until
browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a spoon to break up the mince as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Once the beef is cooked, drain and discard any excess fat, then season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g}, @Central American style spice mix{1%sachet}
and @water{2%tbsp} to the pan. Cook, stirring to combine, for ~{1%minute}.

Stir the @BBQ sauce{32%g} into the pan.

Season with salt and pepper, then remove from the heat.

Lay the @plain taco tortillas{6} (3 per person) onto a lightly oiled #baking
tray{}.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Spoon the beef filling onto one half of each tortilla and top with the cheese.

Fold the other side over to make a semi-circle. Press down to keep together.

Rub each quesadilla with a little oil, then bake on the top shelf of your oven
until golden, ~{8-12%minutes}.

Once ready, transfer the quesadillas to your plates.

Serve the @wild rocket{20%g} on the side.

Serve the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} alongside for dipping. Enjoy!